{|{{Infobox ship begin}} {{Infobox ship image |Ship image= |Ship caption= }} {{Infobox ship career |Hide header= |Ship country=[[Kingdom of Italy (1861–1946)|Italy]] |Ship flag={{shipboxflag|Kingdom of Italy}} |Ship name='''''Flutto''''' |Ship namesake= |Ship ordered= |Ship builder=[[Cantieri Riuniti dell'Adriatico|CRDA]], [[Monfalcone]] |Ship laid down= |Ship launched=19 November 1942 |Ship commissioned= |Ship decommissioned= |Ship in service= |Ship out of service= |Ship struck= |Ship reinstated= |Ship fate=Sunk, 11 July 1943 |Ship status= }} {{Infobox ship characteristics |Hide header= |Header caption= |Ship class= {{sclass-|Flutto|submarine}} |Ship displacement=*{{convert|930|t|LT|0}} surfaced *{{convert|1093|t|LT|0}} submerged |Ship length={{convert|63.15|m|ftin|abbr=on}} |Ship beam={{convert|6.98|m|ftin|abbr=on}} |Ship draft={{convert|4.87|m|ftin|abbr=on}} |Ship power=*{{convert|2400|bhp|lk=in|abbr=on}} (diesels) *{{convert|800|hp|abbr=on}} (electric motors) |Ship propulsion=*[[Diesel-electric]] *2 × [[diesel engine]]s *2 × [[electric motor]]s |Ship speed=*{{convert|16|kn|lk=in}} surfaced *{{convert|8|kn}} submerged |Ship range=*{{convert|5400|nmi|abbr=on|lk=in}} at {{convert|8|kn}} surfaced *{{convert|80|nmi|abbr=on}} at {{convert|4|kn}} submerged |Ship endurance= |Ship test depth={{convert|80|m|ft|abbr=on}} |Ship complement=50 |Ship armament=*6 × {{convert|533|mm|in|0|abbr=on}} [[torpedo tube]]s (4 bow, 2 stern) *1 × [[Škoda 10 cm K10#OTO 100.2F47 History|{{convert|100|mm|in|abbr=on|0}} / 47&nbsp;caliber]] [[deck gun]] *2 × [[Breda Model 35|{{convert|20|mm|in|abbr=on}}]] [[anti-aircraft gun]]s |Ship notes= }} |}
The '''Italian submarine ''Flutto''''' was the [[name ship]] of [[Flutto class submarine|her class]] of [[submarine]]s built for the [[Royal Italian Navy]] (''Regia Marina'') during [[World War II]]. She obtained no successes during her short career, and was sunk by British ships during the [[Invasion of Sicily]] in 1943.
==Design and description== The ''Flutto''-class submarines were designed as improved versions of the preceding {{sclass-|Argo|submarine|4}}. They [[Displacement (ship)|displaced]] {{convert|930|t|LT|sp=us}} surfaced and {{convert|1093|t|LT|sp=us}} submerged. The submarines were {{convert|63.15|m|ftin|sp=us}} long, had a [[beam (nautical)|beam]] of {{convert|6.98|m|ftin|sp=us}} and a [[draft (hull)|draft]] of {{convert|4.87|m|ftin|sp=us}}.<ref name=c5>Chesneau, p. 310</ref>
For surface running, the boats were powered by two {{convert|1200|bhp|lk=in|0|adj=on}} [[diesel engine]]s, each driving one [[propeller shaft]]. When submerged each propeller was driven by a {{convert|400|hp|0|adj=on}} [[electric motor]]. They could reach {{convert|16|kn|lk=in}} on the surface and {{convert|8|kn}} underwater. On the surface, the ''Flutto'' class had a range of {{convert|5400|nmi|lk=in}} at {{convert|8|kn}}, submerged, they had a range of {{convert|80|nmi|abbr=on}} at {{convert|4|kn}}.<ref>Bagnasco, p. 164</ref>
The boats were armed with six internal {{convert|53.3|cm|in|1|abbr=on|sp=us}} [[torpedo tube]]s, four in the bow and two in the stern. One reload were stowed for each tube, which gave them a total of twelve [[torpedo]]es. They were also armed with one [[Škoda 10 cm K10#OTO 100.2F47 History|{{convert|100|mm|in|abbr=on|0}}]] [[deck gun]] and two [[Breda Model 35|{{convert|20|mm|in|abbr=on}}]] anti-aircraft guns for combat on the surface.<ref name=c5/>
==Construction and career== ''Flutto'' was built by [[Cantieri Riuniti dell'Adriatico|CRDA]] at [[Monfalcone]] on the Adriatic coast, and was launched on 19 November 1942. After commissioning and working up ''Flutto'' saw action against Allied naval forces in the Mediterranean. She had no successes, and was lost in action in July 1943 operating against Allied forces involved in [[Operation Husky]], the invasion of [[Sicily]]. On 11 July 1943 ''Flutto'' was on patrol in the [[Straits of Messina]] when she was detected and sunk by three British [[Motor Torpedo Boat]]s (MTB’s ''640'', ''651'' and ''670'') with her entire crew of 49.<ref>Rohwer, p. 262</ref>
== Notes == {{reflist|30em}}
